¶

  • Description: Word Clouds came out to be a game-changer visualization technique for understanding and determining patterns and evolving trends. Whether to discover the political agendas of aspiring election candidates of a country or to analyze the customer reviews on the recently launched product, one can get a visual representation by plotting the Word Cloud.

df_init = pd.read_csv(data_path)
In [4]:
# Get top 10 wines by number of reviews
wines_top = df_init['variety'].value_counts().head(10).index
In [5]:
# Select only colums with description and wine type
df = df_init[df_init['variety'].isin(wines_top)][['description', 'variety']]
In [6]:
# Group all rewies into one string
df = df.groupby(['variety'])['description'].apply(' '.join).reset_index()

Data cleaning¶

In [7]:
# Cleans a string of words.
def search_words(text):
    result = re.findall(r'\b[^\d\W]+\b', text)
    return " ".join(result)
In [10]:
# Clean descriptions to include only words and make the lower case
df['clean'] = df['description'].str.decode('unicode_escape').apply(lambda x : search_words(x.lower()))

Plotting Data¶

In [11]:
# Import mask file
wine_mask = np.array(Image.open("wine_mask.png"))

# Transforms the format of a numpy array
def transform_format(val):
    if val == 0:
        return 255
    else:
        return val

# Transforms the mask so that it works as an outline for the word clouds
transformed_wine_mask = np.ndarray((wine_mask.shape[0],wine_mask.shape[1]), np.int32)

for i in range(len(wine_mask)):
    transformed_wine_mask[i] = list(map(transform_format, wine_mask[i]))
In [13]:
# Get list of stop words
stopwords = nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english')

# Extend stopwords list with wine-related
stopwords.extend(['wine', 'bottle', 'glass', 'grapes', 'pour', 'sip', 'taste', 'flavors', 'show', 
                  'finish', 'note', 'tannins', 'barrel', 'sample', 'drink', 'alcohol', 'Bordeaux'])

# Extend stopwords list with wine names
stopwords.extend(sum([i.split(' ', 1) for i in df['variety'].array], []))

# Make stopwords list lowercase
stopwords = [x.lower() for x in stopwords]
In [14]:
# Creates wordcloud object
def create_word_cloud(text):
    return WordCloud(stopwords=stopwords, background_color="#1d2021", 
        min_word_length=3, max_words=1000, mask=transformed_wine_mask,
        contour_width=3, contour_color='firebrick').generate(text)
In [15]:
# Create wordclouds for all wines in the dataframe
df['cloud'] = df.apply(lambda x: create_word_cloud(x['clean']) ,axis=1)
In [16]:
# Creates a subplot
def create_subplots(rows, columns, index, title, data):
    plt.subplot(rows, columns, index)
    plt.title(title, fontsize = 25, color='white')
    plt.imshow(data, interpolation="bilinear")
    plt.axis("off")
In [17]:
# Plotting the wordclouds
plt.figure(figsize=(50, 50))

df.apply(lambda x: create_subplots(2, 5, x.name + 1, x['variety'], x['cloud']) ,axis=1)

plt.subplots_adjust(hspace = -0.68)
plt.show()
